messages.title: VOTE TO SECURE BRITAIN’S FUTURE ON THURSDAY
messages.content: I am proud to represent you as MP for Witney - supporting our rural economy, protecting our schools and hospitals, improving transport, helping flood victims and fighting your corner in Parliament. This general election, I am not just standing to be your MP but also your Prime Minister for a second term.

keyPolicies.policyDescription: Building a stronger, healthier economy so that everyone can enjoy a decent job, more money at the end of the month, good schools for our children, the security of owning your own home and dignity in retirement.

mentions.tacticalSituation: The choice in this election couldn’t be clearer: stick with a competent, strong Conservative team led by me, your voice in Parliament, and a long-term plan that is working. Or put it all at risk with Ed Miliband as PM and the chaos of more spending, more borrowing and higher taxes.

issues.economy: Our long-term economic plan is building a stronger, healthier economy so that everyone can enjoy a decent job, with more money at the end of the month.

housing.content: The security of owning your own home.

leaflet.personalStatement: I am proud to represent you as MP for Witney.

images.caption: Vote to secure Britain’s future on Thursday

leaflet.additionalNotes: Now more than ever we need strong and competent leadership, not chaos and instability.
